<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN WATER CORP. TO HOST INTERNATIONAL SEMINAR ON DRINKING
WATER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 14 (CNA) 05/14/07  20:29:30 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan Water Corp. (TWC) will host an international seminar
on drinking water systems at National Taiwan University (NTU) May
24-25 in an effort to improve Taiwan's technology and skills in
this regard, a TWC spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 academics and experts from Taiwan, Hong Kong,
Vietnam, Pakistan, Singapore, Japan, Israel, South Korea, America
and Germany will present research papers at the seminar organized
by the NTU's Yen Tjing Ling Industrial Research Institute with
authorization of the TWC, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The seminar will touch upon many topics regarding drinking water
supply systems, including purification plants, benchmarking
systems, water leak control,  water supply  security  and water
source conservation.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, TWC Chairman Hsu Shiang-kueen invited
the NTU's research institute to work out two research plans
dealing with the direction of the TWC.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is under one of the plans titled "Moving Toward
Globalization through International Cooperation and Exchanges, "
the spokesman added.
</P>
